Finding the threshold of history-match error (eHM
) for MER03_SWP, subject to imperfect reservoir model and data measurement. This threshold is denoted by T’. The lines are simulated production curves and the purple squares are historical data. The red rectangles show different T’ values for eHM
of MER03_SWP: 140, 70, and 40.

Ideal scenario of history matching. Each history-match error metric (e

HM
) can find a suite of history-matched models, as illustrated by the red arrows in (a). The final ensemble of history-matched models is the intersection of each individual suite, as illustrated by the yellow shaded area in (b).
